.TH "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_minmax" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_minmax" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_constraint_minmax \- apply a min/max range constraint to an interval
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_constraint_minmax
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_runtime *runtime "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ","
.BI "unsigned int min "  ","
.BI "unsigned int max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "runtime" 12
PCM runtime instance
.IP "var" 12
hw_params variable to apply the range
.IP "min" 12
the minimal value
.IP "max" 12
the maximal value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Apply the min/max range constraint to an interval parameter.
.SH "RETURN"
Positive if the value is changed, zero if it's not changed, or a
negative error code.
